## Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN a launch request with no explicit copilotSessionId
WHEN the launch flow executes
THEN a new RFC 4122 UUID is generated and used as copilotSessionId

GIVEN the launch flow executes with a copilotSessionId
WHEN the launch command is built
THEN the command string contains --resume=<copilotSessionId>

GIVEN the launch flow completes (pane created)
WHEN the manifest is written
THEN it contains copilotSessionId, metadataVersion: 2, and all v2 fields with correct defaults

GIVEN existing launch behavior (autonomous, no v1 params)
WHEN a launch is triggered with default params
THEN existing behavior is preserved — -p flag, -s flag, all existing flags present

GIVEN a v2 manifest is written and then read back
WHEN the read result is inspected
THEN all v2 fields round-trip correctly (no data loss)

