## Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN a launch record with `lastExitType:"ping"` AND a stale ping sidecar at `<stateDir>/exit/<launchId>.json`, WHEN `resumeSubagent({request:{launchId, task:"..."}, services})` is called THEN the stale sidecar is DELETED via `deleteExitSidecar` BEFORE the child resumes (so the parent's next `waitForLaunchCompletion` observes only fresh writes).

GIVEN a resume completes successfully (child writes a new sidecar), WHEN inspecting the launch record THEN `record.pingHistory[last].respondedAt === <ISO>` (the most recent ping entry now has `respondedAt` populated, set when resume was dispatched).

GIVEN a resume relaunches a child, WHEN the new launch is dispatched THEN `record.lastExitType` is reset to `null` (cleared so a fresh terminal state can be recorded by the new completion).

GIVEN a full ping/resume cycle: child writes ping sidecar → parent observes `status:"ping"` → parent calls `resumeSubagent({task})` → child writes done sidecar, WHEN cycle completes THEN parent's final result is `{status:"success", summary:..., launchId}` AND `record.pingHistory.length >= 1` AND `record.pingHistory[0].respondedAt !== null` AND `record.lastExitType === "done"`.

GIVEN the integration test runs end-to-end with stubbed pane/fs services, WHEN executed THEN it completes deterministically without races (no real timers; use injected `now`/`sleep` if needed).

## Implementation Notes

**Stale sidecar cleanup + manifest updates** — in `resumeSubagent` (line 244), AFTER reading the manifest and BEFORE invoking the child:
```js
if (manifest.lastExitType === "ping") {
  deleteExitSidecar({ launchId: manifest.launchId, stateDir, services });
  // Mark the most recent ping as responded
  const pingHistory = [...(manifest.pingHistory ?? [])];
  if (pingHistory.length > 0) {
    pingHistory[pingHistory.length - 1] = {
      ...pingHistory[pingHistory.length - 1],
      respondedAt: services.now?.() ?? new Date().toISOString(),
    };
  }
  // Reset lastExitType so the new launch can record a fresh terminal state
  await stateStore.updateLaunchRecord(manifest.launchId, {
    pingHistory,
    lastExitType: null,
  });
}
```

**Real manifest update API** is `stateStore.updateLaunchRecord(launchId, updates)` at `lib/state.mjs:118-126` — the `updates` object spreads onto the existing record. (Do NOT use `updateRecord` — that does not exist.)

